The paper deals with the capacity of a discrete-time multi-input multi-output (MIMO) Gaussian channel with output quantization, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses different analog receiver architectures for MIMO channels, which falls under the category of signal processing (cs.SP). The use of analog combiners and sign quantizers for analog/digital conversion suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of networked systems (cs.NI) and machine learning (cs.MM). Finally, the paper's focus on optimizing capacity suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-category of statistical learning (cs.SI).
